## What Are We Doing? (Simple Explanation)

We are building a **smart automatic ticket system for IT support teams. 

The Problem: When someone has a computer problem (broken printer, lost password, etc.), the IT team receives tickets. Right now:
- Tickets go to the wrong team (wrong routing)
- People wait too long for help
- The same problems get solved again and again
- Support staff are overworked

Our Solution: We will build 4 robot assistants that work together to:
1. Read the problem (ticket)
2. Understand what type of problem it is (classify)
3. Send it to the right team (route)
4. Give step-by-step instructions to fix it (resolve)
5. Check if they should ask a human for help (escalate)

All of this happens in seconds, not hours!

