## Data Model (Database Design)

### Ticket Entity (What information about each ticket)
```
Ticket
├── ticket_id (unique number, like T-2001)
├── description (what the user typed)
├── category (Hardware, Software, Network, Security, HR/IT Access)
├── subcategory (Printer, Monitor, etc)
├── priority (Low, Medium, High, Critical)
├── department (Hardware Support, DevOps, etc)
├── resolved (yes/no)
├── resolution_steps (list of fix instructions)
├── confidence_score (0.0 to 1.0)
└── escalate (yes/no - needs human?)
```

### Relationships
```
One Ticket → Goes to One Department
One Department → Has Many Support Teams
One Ticket → Has Many Resolution Steps
```

